</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="446" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,974]" pageId="45" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,877,902]" pageId="45" pageNumber="446">Comments:</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[638,780,877,902]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Cardiacephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arthritica">
<emphasis box="[638,780,877,902]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="446">C. arthritica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with a striking white fore tarsomere one. The paired spermathecae is also much broadened and the appendix at the ultimate portion of the paired spermathecal duct stem is conspicuously longer.
</paragraph>
